# HTSA enrollment invoices — NEW pages only

**Never** edit an existing client’s deployed `htsa-enrollment-*.html` to create a **new** person. **`cp`** a frozen file from **`templates/htsa-placement-*.html`** (see table below) or another modern invoice, then replace **only** the new file. Reference invoices (Zachary, Trameil, Val, Thomas, Jocelyn layout, CJ practice, Margarita, etc.) are **read-only** unless CJ explicitly asks to edit a named file. See **`templates/README.md`** for copy-paste prompts.

---

## CJ paste shortcut (primary on-call flow)

When CJ pastes **only** a block in this shape (blank lines OK), **do not** ask them to type long shell commands. **Parse the block, map placement, normalize phone to E.164, run instantiate with `--overwrite --ship`, wait for script output `READY`, then return the live URL** (never before `READY` — avoids GitHub Pages 404).

**Canonical paste:**

```text
Full Name

Email: client@example.com

Phone Number: +1 (555) 123-4567

Setter - Cash only
```

**Program line** (usually last): CJ may type **plain English** matching the six rows (`Closer – Cash only`, `Setter - Cash + Financing`, `Closer & Setter – Cash only`, etc.) **or** `templates/htsa-placement-0X-….html` **or** both joined with ` or ` (prefer the `templates/…` segment when the file exists).

**Mapping:** Closer cash only → `01` · Closer cash + financing → `02` · Setter cash only → `03` · Setter cash + financing → `04` · Dual cash only → `05` · Dual cash + financing → `06`.

**Implementation:** From repo root, either (a) run **`htsa`** in Terminal (shell function in CJ’s `~/.zshrc` — paste block, **Ctrl-D**, wait for **`READY`**), (b) run `python3 scripts/htsa-paste-invoice.py` with the block on **stdin** (ends with Ctrl-D), which calls **`htsa-instantiate-invoice.py`** with **`--overwrite --ship`** by default, or (c) parse manually and invoke the same.

**Terminal (free — no Agent):** `htsa` → paste canonical block → **Ctrl-D**. Do **not** paste the block alone at the shell `%` prompt (zsh will treat each line as a command). Cursor uses **zsh (login)** so `htsa` auto-loads from `~/.htsa-shell/htsa.zsh` — open a **new** Terminal tab after setup (close old tabs that still say `command not found`).

**Respect explicit “do not touch”:** If CJ says an invoice is **already perfect** or **do not redo** a named file, **do not** overwrite that HTML.

